library(sp)
library(rworldmap)
## ### Welcome to rworldmap ###
## For a short introduction type :   vignette('rworldmap')
data = read.csv("fifa.csv")
fifa = data[,which(names(data)%in%c("Nationality","Age","Overall","Potential"))]

library(stringr)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("Bosnia Herzegovina",'Bosnia and Herzegovina',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("China PR",'China',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("Central African Rep.",'Central African Republic',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("Antigua & Barbuda",'Antigua and Barbuda',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("DR Congo",'Congo, the Democratic Republic of the',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("England",'United Kingdom',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("FYR Macedonia",'Macedonia, the former Yugoslav Republic of',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("Guinea Bissau",'Guinea-Bissau',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("Ivory Coast","Cte d'Ivoire",fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("Korea Republic",'Korea, Republic of (South Korea)',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("Northern Ireland",'United Kingdom',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("Republic of Ireland",'Ireland',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("Scotland",'United Kingdom',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("Korea DPR","Korea, Democratic People's Republic of",fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("St Kitts Nevis",'Saint Kitts and Nevis',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("St Lucia",'Saint Lucia',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("United States",'United States Of America',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("Wales",'United Kingdom',fifa$Nationality)
fifa$Nationality <- gsub("Trinidad & Tobago",'Trinidad and Tobago',fifa$Nationality) 
code = read.csv("iso.csv",stringsAsFactors = F, header = T )
code = code[,c(1,3)]
df = merge(fifa,code,by.x = "Nationality", by.y = "English.short.name.lower.case", all.x = T)
df = na.omit(df)
library(plyr)
count = count(df,vars ="Alpha.3.code" )
mapped_data <- joinCountryData2Map(count, joinCode = "ISO3", nameJoinColumn = "Alpha.3.code")
## 149 codes from your data successfully matched countries in the map
## 0 codes from your data failed to match with a country code in the map
## 94 codes from the map weren't represented in your data
par(mai=c(0,0,0.5,0),xaxs="i",yaxs="i")
mapCountryData(mapped_data, nameColumnToPlot = "freq")

mean = aggregate(df[, 2:4], list(df$Alpha.3.code), mean)
age = mean[,c(1,2)]
overall = mean[,c(1,3)]
potential = mean[,c(1,4)]
Age <- joinCountryData2Map(age, joinCode = "ISO3", nameJoinColumn = "Group.1")
## 149 codes from your data successfully matched countries in the map
## 0 codes from your data failed to match with a country code in the map
## 94 codes from the map weren't represented in your data
Overall <- joinCountryData2Map(overall, joinCode = "ISO3", nameJoinColumn = "Group.1")
## 149 codes from your data successfully matched countries in the map
## 0 codes from your data failed to match with a country code in the map
## 94 codes from the map weren't represented in your data
Potential <- joinCountryData2Map(potential, joinCode = "ISO3", nameJoinColumn = "Group.1")
## 149 codes from your data successfully matched countries in the map
## 0 codes from your data failed to match with a country code in the map
## 94 codes from the map weren't represented in your data
par(mai=c(0,0,0.5,0),xaxs="i",yaxs="i")
mapCountryData(Age, nameColumnToPlot = "Age")

par(mai=c(0,0,0.5,0),xaxs="i",yaxs="i")
mapCountryData(Overall, nameColumnToPlot = "Overall")

par(mai=c(0,0,0.5,0),xaxs="i",yaxs="i")
mapCountryData(Potential, nameColumnToPlot = "Potential")
